SQLite Interrogation Methods

### One-liner

```bash
sqlite3 var/app-instance/dev.db "
  .headers on
  .mode column
  SELECT id, slice, type, happened_at_utc, prev_hash, event_hash
  FROM transactions_ledger
  ORDER BY happened_at_utc ASC, id ASC
  LIMIT 25;
"
```

### Interactive session

```bash
sqlite3 var/app-instance/dev.db
.headers on
.mode column
SELECT id, slice, type, happened_at_utc, prev_hash, event_hash
FROM transactions_ledger
ORDER BY happened_at_utc ASC, id ASC
LIMIT 25;
.quit
```

### Python (no sqlite3 CLI needed)

```bash
python - <<'PY'
from app import create_app
from app.extensions import db
from sqlalchemy import text
app = create_app("config.DevConfig")
with app.app_context():
    rows = db.session.execute(text("""
        SELECT id, slice, type, happened_at_utc, prev_hash, event_hash
        FROM transactions_ledger
        ORDER BY happened_at_utc ASC, id ASC
        LIMIT 25
    """)).all()
    for r in rows:
        print(r)
PY
```

Since `verify_ledger_chain.py` is green, you’re good. The `ORDER BY …` examples are just for spot-checking if you want to inspect rows yourself.
